Vice President Mike Pence visited Indiana to attend an announcement by Infosys Technologies Ltd., an Indian IT company, that it will be expanding and creating jobs in the state. Pence praised Governor Eric Holcomb and President Donald Trump for their leadership in promoting economic growth. He highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration, including rolling back regulations, promoting American energy, and implementing tax cuts. Pence also mentioned other companies, such as FedEx, Foxconn, and Apple, that have recently made significant investments in the Midwest. He thanked Infosys for its commitment to hiring American workers and praised Indiana's pro-business environment. Pence concluded by expressing his belief that the best days for Indiana and America are yet to come.